CRITICAL-002: Fix Integer Underflow in Stock Calculation
========================================================

ISSUE:
-------
When deducting stock, no underflow check exists. If a malicious or corrupted
request contains UINT64_MAX as quantity, the validation passes but calculation
wraps around, corrupting stock data:

  Current Stock: 10
  Requested: UINT64_MAX - 5
  Validation: 10 < (UINT64_MAX - 5) = true, passes!
  Calculation: 10 - (UINT64_MAX - 5) = wraps to huge positive number
  Result: DATA CORRUPTION

FILE: apps/backend/internal/repositories/transaction_repository_impl.go
LINE: 352-363

FIX APPLIED:
------------
1. Use int64 for all stock arithmetic (not uint)
2. Check for negative result BEFORE assigning back to uint field
3. Add defensive underflow detection
4. Use explicit stock value assignment instead of += expression

PATCH:
-------
```diff
--- a/apps/backend/internal/repositories/transaction_repository_impl.go
+++ b/apps/backend/internal/repositories/transaction_repository_impl.go
@@ -350,15 +350,26 @@ func (r *transactionRepository) ProcessSaleWithStockUpdate(ctx context.Context,
 				return fmt.Errorf("failed to lock product %d: %w", productID, err)
 			}

-			// Check if sufficient stock is available
-			if product.StockQty + delta < 0 {
+			// CRITICAL-002 FIX: Use int64 arithmetic to prevent integer overflow/underflow
+			// Cast to int64 first, then check for negative result
+			currentStock := int64(product.StockQty)
+			newStock := currentStock + delta
+
+			// Check if sufficient stock is available (newStock must be >= 0)
+			if newStock < 0 {
 				return fmt.Errorf("insufficient stock for product %s (ID: %d). Available: %d, Requested: %d",
-					product.Name, productID, product.StockQty, -delta)
+					product.Name, productID, product.StockQty, -delta)
 			}

-			// Update stock
+			// Defensive: Detect underflow (new stock should be less than or equal to current when deducting)
+			if delta < 0 && newStock > currentStock {
+				return fmt.Errorf("stock calculation error: underflow detected for product %s (ID: %d)",
+					product.Name, productID)
+			}
+
+			// Update stock with validated int64 value
 			if err := tx.Model(&models.Product{}).
 				Where("id = ?", productID).
-				Update("stock_qty", gorm.Expr("stock_qty + ?", delta)).Error; err != nil {
+				Update("stock_qty", newStock).Error; err != nil {
 				return fmt.Errorf("failed to update stock for product %d: %w", productID, err)
 			}
 		}
```

ADDITIONAL PROTECTION:
---------------------
Add input validation at handler level to reject unreasonably large quantities:

```diff
--- a/apps/backend/internal/handlers/transaction_handler.go
+++ b/apps/backend/internal/handlers/transaction_handler.go
@@ -90,6 +90,16 @@ func (h *TransactionHandler) CreateTransaction(c *gin.Context) {
 			})
 			return
 		}
+
+		// CRITICAL-002: Validate item quantities to prevent integer overflow attacks
+		const maxQuantity = 10000 // Reasonable upper bound for single product quantity
+		for _, item := range saleRequest.Items {
+			if item.Quantity <= 0 || item.Quantity > maxQuantity {
+				c.JSON(http.StatusBadRequest, middleware.RFC7807Error{
+					Type:     "https://api.simpo.com/errors/invalid-quantity",
+					Title:    "Invalid Quantity",
+					Status:   http.StatusBadRequest,
+					Detail:   "Jumlah produk harus antara 1 dan 10000",
+					Instance: c.Request.URL.Path,
+				})
+				return
+			}
+		}

 		// Process sale with transactional operations
 		transaction, err := h.transactionService.ProcessSale(c.Request.Context(), &saleRequest, cashierID, branchID)
```

